claim.claim-text:
17. A steering yoke comprising:
a hollow cylindrical body formed from a laminated sheet of metal and polymer, the hollow cylindrical body having a substantially uniform wall thickness and including a first half, a second half, a seam extending at least partially along the body between the first half and the second half, an upper end having a surface, and a lower open end, wherein at least a portion of the first and second halves form an outer perimeter of the steering yoke;
at least one weld extending along the seam joining the first half and the second half;
a bearing surface coupled to the surface of the upper end of the hollow cylindrical body; and
a spring perch disposed in the lower end of the hollow cylindrical body, wherein the spring perch includes a spring pocket configured to support and retain a spring for supplying a biasing force to the yoke.
